main event: On 7th June 1956, at Olmstead AFB in Pennsylvania, a circular object with flame-colored features was observed hovering overhead for 5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as circular with flame-colored features, and it hovered overhead for 5 minutes.
The report lacks sufficient data for analysis, and the conclusions drawn from the observation are unknown.
The observation was made from the ground with no photographs available.
The sighting occurred at 0322Z and the location was Eastern Sol Holafied Ave in Pennsylvania.
The weather and winds-aloft conditions at the time and place of the sighting were detailed in the report.
